risation des connecteurs qui souligne leur fonction constructive textuelle et discursive.  aThis study undertakes a systematic analysis of French prepositional connectors. It explains the tendency of prepositions to form connectors and provides a model of complementary semantic and pragmatic categories covering the types, functions, and usage of connectors across a variety of genres.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aFrench languagexConnectives. 0aFrench languagexPrepositions. 4aDiskursanalyse. 4aDiskursmarker. 4aKonnektor. 4aPräposition. 4aSprachwandel. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Semantics.2bisacsh  aDiscourse Analysis.  aDiscourse Markers, Connectors.  aLanguage Change.  aPrepositions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK 2013z9783110317237oZDB-23-DSP0 cprintz978311030068040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030130440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110301304423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110301304/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2013